Hey, about the project timeline you asked for. I've mapped out the next three phases based on our discussion yesterday. The first phase involves finalizing the user research synthesis, which should wrap up by Wednesday. We'll then present those findings to the design team on Thursday morning. The second phase is the prototyping sprint, which we've scheduled for the following week. I've blocked out time with the developers for a brief integration check on Tuesday of that week. The third phase is the usability testing round. We've recruited five participants so far and are looking for a few more to get a good mix. Let me know if you want to sit in on any of the test sessions. I think the afternoon slots on Wednesday or Friday would be best for observation. Also, don't forget to review the updated brand guidelines document I shared in the shared drive. There are a few minor typography changes we need to align on before the final prototype handoff. I'll send a separate email about the lo
 gistics for the team off-site next month. We need to decide on a final location. The options are the lakeside lodge or the downtown conference center. Each has its pros and cons regarding travel time and cost. I'm leaning towards the lodge for the quieter environment, but I know some people prefer being in the city. What's your initial thought? We should probably take a quick poll.

A
