Your Courtesy Roadside Kit is Ready

Provided for eligible residents in your locality.

As a licensed driver residing in a participating region, you qualify for a Roadside Support Kit through the local community program. This kit is provided at no charge to eligible residents. You will not be billed for the kit.

Access Your Kit Details

The kit contains practical items to assist with common roadside situations. Supplies are allocated based on program participation levels in your area.

Reflective Safety Vest

Multi-Tool with Pliers

USB-Powered Jumper Cables

Tire Pressure Gauge

Compact First Aid Supplies

LED Flashlight with Batteries

Emergency Blanket

Nylon Towing Strap

Waterproof Document Pouch

Work Gloves

Portable Phone Charger

Basic Repair Tape Roll

This offering is made available through regional program participation. Kit availability is subject to local allocation.

Thank you for being part of our community. We are pleased to provide this support resource.

Regarding the garden plans for the spring, I think we should start with the raised beds on the south side. The soil there gets the most sun and has good drainage. We can plant tomatoes, peppers, and basil in those. For the shadier north corner, lettuce and spinach would do well. I've already ordered the seeds from that catalog we looked at. The delivery should arrive next week. We'll also need to get some fresh compost. The local nursery has a good blend they make themselves. I can pick up a few bags on Saturday morning. Do you want to come along? We could also look at trellis options for the peas and cucumbers. I saw a simple wooden design that would be easy to build. I have some spare lumber in the garage that might work. Let me know what day is good for you to work on that project. Maybe Sunday afternoon? Also, have you decided what to do about the patio furniture? The covers from last year are looking pretty worn. We could try to clean them, or just invest in new ones. There's a 
 sale at the home store until the end of the month. I can check the prices if you want. Another thing, the neighbor mentioned their apple tree might need pruning soon. They asked if we knew anyone. I told them I'd ask you for a recommendation.

